Dialogue: 0,0:00:21.85,0:00:23.55,Narration Off,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Today's code is hard to solve!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:23.55,0:00:25.15,Narration Off,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Stars and criminals are both called "{\i1}hoshi{\i0}"!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:25.15,0:00:26.95,Narration Off,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Look through the telescope!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:26.95,0:00:28.45,Narration Off,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}He sees the single truth for what it is,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:28.45,0:00:30.15,Narration Off,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}and looks like a kid but has the mind of an adult.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:30.15,0:00:32.25,Narration Off,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}His name? Detective Conan!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:55.95,0:02:00.05,Narration Off,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}We came to a hostel in the mountains to observe the stars.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:01.25,0:02:06.15,Narration Off,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Along with the hostel's owner, Ryoji Amatsuchi{\rHonorifics - Narration Off\be10}-san{\r\be10}, we met
Dialogue: 0,0:02:06.15,0:02:07.45,Narration Off,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Etsuko Nonomiya{\rHonorifics - Narration Off\be10}-san{\r\be10},
Dialogue: 0,0:02:08.05,0:02:09.25,Narration Off,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Hajime Futagawa{\rHonorifics - Narration Off\be10}-san{\r\be10},
Dialogue: 0,0:02:09.65,0:02:11.15,Narration Off,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}and Heihachi Mikami{\rHonorifics - Narration Off\be10}-san{\r\be10}, who had been invited.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:12.42,0:02:16.65,Narration Off,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}And somehow, when we had gone to a nearby hill to look at the stars,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:16.85,0:02:18.85,Narration Off,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}we found a dead body that was reduced to bones.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:19.25,0:02:23.35,Narration Off,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}And in his hand he left six cigarettes as a dying message.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:24.75,0:02:25.75,Narration Off,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Then, that night...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:25.75,0:02:26.75,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,What was that sound just now?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:28.85,0:02:29.65,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Futagawa{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}?!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:32.45,0:02:34.75,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Is it the same dying message again?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:35.25,0:02:37.15,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,No. This time...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:37.85,0:02:39.25,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,there's one more cigarette!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:50.05,0:02:51.32,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You're right!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:51.32,0:02:53.37,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Now there are seven cigarettes!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:53.37,0:02:55.15,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,What does it mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:55.43,0:02:56.75,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,My first guess...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:57.12,0:02:58.77,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,is that the six cigarettes
Dialogue: 0,0:02:59.11,0:03:04.41,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,left by Kono{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} who was killed a year ago, that we found earlier today,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:04.85,0:03:08.32,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,and these seven cigarettes we found with Futagawa{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r},
Dialogue: 0,0:03:08.60,0:03:10.65,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,point to two different people.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:11.05,0:03:17.19,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Maybe it's a fake message the killer forced into his hand to confuse the investigation.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:17.19,0:03:18.45,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't think so.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:18.97,0:03:23.72,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,We came running over here because we heard something fall.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:24.63,0:03:28.45,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You didn't see a flashlight or anything when we ran over here, did you?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:29.22,0:03:30.45,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It was pitch dark.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:30.81,0:03:35.65,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Then Kono{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} and Futagawa{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s killers were different people...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:35.92,0:03:39.65,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Or else Futagawa{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} left this hint behind for some reason...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:41.25,0:03:42.63,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}One cigarette has blood on it!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:44.02,0:03:45.79,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}So does the cigarette carton he's holding in his hand!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:49.05,0:03:51.45,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}On this other carton in his pocket...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:52.87,0:03:54.25,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}This could mean...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:59.77,0:04:01.45,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Your Detective Badge is beeping!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:04.53,0:04:08.10,Radio,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}It's me! Can you see me? Look above you!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:08.45,0:04:09.92,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, Doc!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:12.45,0:04:14.45,Radio,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Hey, did you see anybody up there?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:14.75,0:04:16.08,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Nope, nobody.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:16.08,0:04:18.15,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Nobody here but us.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:18.35,0:04:20.65,Radio,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}But we {\i1}did{\i0} find something someone left behind.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:21.02,0:04:22.00,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Left behind?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:22.28,0:04:23.25,Radio,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}It's a cell phone.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:24.30,0:04:26.55,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,And there's an unsent message on it.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:26.87,0:04:28.25,Radio,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Hey, what does it say?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:30.55,0:04:31.25,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,"My last words".
Dialogue: 0,0:04:32.15,0:04:33.95,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}D-Did you say "last words"?!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:35.05,0:04:37.55,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Futagawa{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s dead?!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:38.14,0:04:39.65,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,That can't be!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:40.51,0:04:43.25,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,He fell off the cliff. Looks like death was instantaneous.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:43.68,0:04:47.91,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,And we found his cell phone on top of the cliff,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:48.65,0:04:51.75,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,with a "last words" text message, and no destination attached.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:52.55,0:04:54.20,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Last words on his phone?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:54.55,0:04:56.74,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Here's what he wrote in the text.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:56.95,0:04:59.32,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,"I invited everyone to this hostel..."
Dialogue: 0,0:04:59.55,0:05:05.05,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,"to make a confession about what I did to you when we were all here a year ago."
Dialogue: 0,0:05:05.33,0:05:11.00,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,"That's right. The one who killed Asao Kono{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} one year ago was me, Hajime Futagawa."
Dialogue: 0,0:05:11.59,0:05:13.95,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,"Etsuko Nonomiya{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, his fiancée,"
Dialogue: 0,0:05:14.52,0:05:17.51,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,"I'm sorry for killing the man you loved."
Dialogue: 0,0:05:18.52,0:05:21.67,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,"Ryoji Amatsuchi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, Kono{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s {\i1}sempai{\i0} at university,"
Dialogue: 0,0:05:21.95,0:05:26.40,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,"I apologize for tainting your wonderful hostel."
Dialogue: 0,0:05:26.86,0:05:28.99,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,"And Editor-in-Chief Heihachi Mikami,"
Dialogue: 0,0:05:29.47,0:05:33.15,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,"please take good care of {\i1}Space Sunday{\i0} after I'm gone."
Dialogue: 0,0:05:33.83,0:05:38.85,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,"He and I got into an argument on top of the cliff."
Dialogue: 0,0:05:39.13,0:05:42.05,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,"I shoved him, and he lost his balance and fell."
Dialogue: 0,0:05:42.05,0:05:45.85,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,"I was going to confess and beg for your mercy,"
Dialogue: 0,0:05:45.85,0:05:47.81,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,"but I just couldn't bring myself to say the words."
Dialogue: 0,0:05:48.53,0:05:52.65,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,"I will pay with my life before the police arrive tomorrow."
Dialogue: 0,0:05:52.65,0:05:54.30,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,"— Hajime Futagawa."
Dialogue: 0,0:05:55.14,0:05:56.12,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Then he...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:56.60,0:05:58.98,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Asao is... Asao really is...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:59.80,0:06:03.31,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sorry. As his boss, let me apologize.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:04.60,0:06:06.15,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't cry, Etchan.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:06.77,0:06:12.20,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,But at least now we know why he disappeared, and who's responsible.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:12.40,0:06:15.65,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,But why would a person committing suicide...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:16.14,0:06:17.63,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,leave something like this behind?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:20.72,0:06:25.01,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,We found those seven cigarettes the old guy had in his hand when he died!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:25.76,0:06:29.75,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Kono{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} had six, and he had one more long one!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:32.40,0:06:34.88,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,If Futagawa{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} committed suicide
Dialogue: 0,0:06:35.34,0:06:39.20,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,after realizing that his message pointed back to him,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:39.20,0:06:41.55,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,why did he add another cigarette?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:42.88,0:06:45.86,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Furthermore, why was there blood on the additional cigarette?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:46.57,0:06:52.95,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,There was also blood on Futagawa{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s hand, and on the cigarette carton in his pocket.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.90,0:06:57.55,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,There were signs he had been struck on the head with a steel pipe.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:57.73,0:06:59.15,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Struck?!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:59.99,0:07:04.66,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The blood on his hand was probably from holding it to his bleeding head.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:05.28,0:07:07.15,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,In other words, those seven cigarettes were...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:07.60,0:07:10.34,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,from when somebody on the cliff struck Futagawa{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r},
Dialogue: 0,0:07:10.72,0:07:14.15,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,then stole his cell phone to type a fake suicide note.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:14.42,0:07:18.05,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,While he lay there, Futagawa{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} took a cigarette from his own carton,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:18.52,0:07:22.60,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,and added it to the six cigarettes in the other carton,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:23.00,0:07:25.45,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,most likely, I think, as a dying message.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:26.01,0:07:27.05,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,N-No...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:27.29,0:07:30.00,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It's safe to assume he created the carton with six cigarettes
Dialogue: 0,0:07:30.44,0:07:34.75,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,while trying to figure out whether Kono{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s message was pointing to him.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:34.75,0:07:36.28,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,W-Wait a minute!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:36.56,0:07:39.10,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,With seven cigarettes, you can spell Amatsuchi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s name...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:39.10,0:07:41.55,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Doesn't that make {\i1}you{\i0} the killer?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:42.00,0:07:42.85,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,H-Hey!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:43.40,0:07:47.15,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Mikami{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s first name, Heihachi, can be spelled with seven cigarettes too.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:49.13,0:07:51.99,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Your initials can be spelled with seven cigarettes too, isn't that right,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:52.45,0:07:53.63,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Etsuko Nonomiya{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:54.74,0:07:56.85,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Now, now, keep your cool...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:57.17,0:08:00.66,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,So none of you saw each other in the woods?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:00.66,0:08:01.09,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Not me.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:01.09,0:08:01.55,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,No.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:02.41,0:08:04.76,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Then let's try searching our rooms.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:06.15,0:08:09.79,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The thin, steel pipe-like object Futagawa{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} was hit with has been hidden.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:10.14,0:08:13.28,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,After all, the killer could use it to strike again.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:14.70,0:08:17.55,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, hey, don't turn the place upside-down!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:18.35,0:08:21.65,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, you brought your own telescope?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:21.94,0:08:24.45,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, it belongs to the editorial office.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:24.71,0:08:28.55,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Lens barrel, mount, scope, tripod...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:29.21,0:08:32.91,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The barrel of a telescope isn't hard enough to knock someone out.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:33.17,0:08:37.15,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,And a tripod like that would just bend in half.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:37.48,0:08:38.55,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,He's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:38.97,0:08:39.56,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:39.90,0:08:42.74,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You were trying to figure things out with cigarettes too?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:42.92,0:08:43.45,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:44.08,0:08:46.25,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,But I wasn't able to solve it.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:47.60,0:08:49.85,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, will you cut that out?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:50.18,0:08:51.64,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,How long are you going to search my room?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:52.45,0:08:55.45,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The only thing that could be used as a weapon is this umbrella.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:55.45,0:08:57.74,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,But there are no dents in it...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:58.15,0:09:01.45,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Of course not! I'm not the murderer!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:01.92,0:09:04.83,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, where's that bottle of booze you had with you?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:06.01,0:09:07.25,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I threw it away in the woods...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:07.65,0:09:09.65,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,while I was waiting for you guys to pass by me.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:10.01,0:09:11.25,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Pass by?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:11.85,0:09:13.67,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You came after me, didn't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:13.99,0:09:17.05,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You, the boy with the freckles, and the little girl with the bobbed hair.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:17.43,0:09:21.60,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I was busy throwing up behind a tree.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:27.10,0:09:31.55,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Looks like you were trying to solve Kono{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s dying message too.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:31.77,0:09:35.79,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes. But I never guessed it stood for that Futagawa guy's initials.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:36.48,0:09:38.98,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I didn't know his first name anyway.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:40.94,0:09:44.23,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,All that's left, Amatsuchi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, is you.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:44.57,0:09:47.78,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,But this whole hostel is like your room...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:48.05,0:09:51.27,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,so we'll leave it to the police when we've called them in the morning.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:51.27,0:09:51.95,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:52.64,0:09:56.07,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You should advise the cops to search the woods.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:56.60,0:09:59.25,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,If I were the killer, that's where I'd get rid of the weapon.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:59.58,0:10:00.70,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Uh, right.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:01.79,0:10:03.55,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, Haibara? Any luck?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:03.99,0:10:06.67,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I searched every corner of Futagawa{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s room,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:06.67,0:10:07.95,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,but I couldn't find it.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:08.41,0:10:11.25,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The thing you told me to look for.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:11.90,0:10:15.60,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Weird. If the murderer left that fake suicide note before killing him,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:15.60,0:10:16.89,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,it's gotta be around here somewhere.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:16.89,0:10:17.35,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Uh...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:18.55,0:10:20.65,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,While you were searching the rooms,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:20.97,0:10:23.23,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,we kept an eye on the people waiting here.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:23.70,0:10:26.35,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,That Amatsuchi guy's acting suspicious!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:26.35,0:10:28.45,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, very suspicious!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:28.74,0:10:29.32,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,How so?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:29.32,0:10:31.95,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,He kept looking at the guestbook!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:32.49,0:10:34.09,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Over and over again!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:34.40,0:10:36.55,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,With a scary look on his face, like this!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:37.55,0:10:38.75,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The guestbook?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:39.29,0:10:43.25,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Come to think of it, Mikami{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} and Futagawa{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} said
Dialogue: 0,0:10:44.54,0:10:46.15,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,that they had only met Kono{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} once.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:46.53,0:10:50.72,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,But it looks like they've stayed here several times since Kono{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} disappeared.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:51.31,0:10:52.02,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, I found it!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:52.36,0:10:53.55,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,This must be the day!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:54.06,0:10:56.05,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The day that Kono person died!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:56.66,0:10:57.45,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I think you're right...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:57.91,0:11:00.47,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,After Kono{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} and Nonomiya{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s names,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:00.77,0:11:02.69,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,there's Mikami{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} and Futagawa{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:03.07,0:11:04.15,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,This is it, all right.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:04.65,0:11:06.01,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Could it be?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:09.45,0:11:11.52,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}I see, that's what it means!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:14.63,0:11:16.43,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, Haibara...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:22.65,0:11:24.05,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm counting on you.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:25.78,0:11:27.66,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I got a favor to ask of Ayumi too.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:27.66,0:11:28.55,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Right, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:28.93,0:11:30.62,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,A Fusae brand wallet.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:30.62,0:11:31.85,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,That's my price.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:31.85,0:11:34.25,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Do we have a deal?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:34.75,0:11:35.85,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Oh, for the love of...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:36.65,0:11:38.45,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Ow!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:39.75,0:11:41.85,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Haibara{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}! What's the matter?!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:42.40,0:11:43.70,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Are you okay, Ai{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-chan{\r}?!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:43.70,0:11:44.50,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Haibara!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:45.40,0:11:47.57,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,This looks serious! She may have appendicitis!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:47.57,0:11:49.83,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,What? You're in pain, Ai{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:50.12,0:11:52.85,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,What should we do? The phone's out...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:52.85,0:11:56.16,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,and who knows how many hours it'll take to carry her down the mountain?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:56.16,0:11:56.76,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Haibara!!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:56.76,0:11:58.45,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It hurts, Doctor...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:58.45,0:12:00.65,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Doctor, do something!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:02.95,0:12:04.53,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Ow!!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:05.13,0:12:06.77,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Doctor...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:14.22,0:12:16.75,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Hello? Could you send an ambulance, please?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:17.12,0:12:18.95,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, a child has suddenly—
Dialogue: 0,0:12:19.76,0:12:20.90,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Just as I thought.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:30.00,0:12:32.00,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Hello? Could you send an ambulance, please?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:32.60,0:12:33.70,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,What? Oh no!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:33.70,0:12:36.70,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,But I thought the phone cable was missing.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:37.10,0:12:39.80,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,T-The address is...Gunma Prefecture...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:45.50,0:12:46.30,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}?!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:46.30,0:12:48.80,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,If we don't call an ambulance, Ai{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-chan{\r} will...!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:48.80,0:12:50.30,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,What are you doing?!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:50.40,0:12:52.70,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,No need. It was just an act.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:53.40,0:12:55.40,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,We wanted to smoke out the person
Dialogue: 0,0:12:55.80,0:12:58.00,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,who hid the phone cable
Dialogue: 0,0:12:59.00,0:13:00.70,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,and let the air out of everyone's tires
Dialogue: 0,0:13:00.70,0:13:03.00,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,to keep us trapped here.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:03.80,0:13:06.80,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You don't mean, the person who sent the invitations
Dialogue: 0,0:13:06.90,0:13:09.10,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,summoning us here under Asao's name was...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:09.20,0:13:10.50,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It was you?!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:10.90,0:13:13.90,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,So the one who left the suicide note on Futagawa{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s cell phone
Dialogue: 0,0:13:14.20,0:13:17.70,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,and pushed him off the cliff to make it look like a suicide
Dialogue: 0,0:13:18.00,0:13:20.65,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,was {\i1}you{\i0}, Ryoji Amatsuchi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:20.65,0:13:21.50,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Uh, er...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:28.80,0:13:29.80,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Nope.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:31.80,0:13:32.90,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,"Nope"?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:33.00,0:13:35.10,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Amatsuchi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} {\i1}is{\i0} the one who sent the invitations
Dialogue: 0,0:13:35.10,0:13:37.50,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,and got us stuck here,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:37.80,0:13:39.30,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,but he isn't the murderer.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:39.70,0:13:41.30,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,How come, Conan?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:41.60,0:13:44.70,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Remember that suicide note left on the cell phone?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:45.30,0:13:47.50,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It just said, "I invited everyone to this hostel."
Dialogue: 0,0:13:48.00,0:13:51.10,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,If Amatsuchi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} had been Futagawa{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s killer,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:51.30,0:13:53.50,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,he would have tried to make us think
Dialogue: 0,0:13:54.20,0:13:56.80,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,that Futagawa{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} was {\i1}also{\i0} the one who trapped us here, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:57.30,0:13:57.90,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Besides,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:58.00,0:14:03.10,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,he could have planted the phone cable in Futagawa{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s clothes, or his room.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:03.20,0:14:04.60,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I-I see...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:05.10,0:14:07.30,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Amatsuchi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} summoned everyone to the hostel
Dialogue: 0,0:14:07.90,0:14:10.00,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,because he found the bones of Kono{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r},
Dialogue: 0,0:14:10.20,0:14:11.70,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,who died here a year ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:12.10,0:14:15.60,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,He had found the ring and the dying message with the cigarettes.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:16.50,0:14:19.20,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,That's how you knew, after just glimpsing them,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:19.70,0:14:24.00,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,that there were exactly four long ones and two short ones, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:24.70,0:14:30.60,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,That's right. I sent the invitations after finding the bones to those who were here that day.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:31.40,0:14:34.40,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I thought that once it got out that the bones and the message had been discovered,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:34.80,0:14:37.80,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,the killer would confess.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:38.00,0:14:41.60,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,But when Futagawa{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} died, I was afraid to admit it.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:41.70,0:14:44.90,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,So in that case, the one who killed Futagawa{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:45.20,0:14:46.30,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Ain't it obvious?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:46.50,0:14:49.60,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Maybe it's that Nonomiya lady?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:49.70,0:14:50.80,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,How could you...?!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:52.00,0:14:53.40,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It's a possibility.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:53.80,0:14:57.50,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,If she figured out the cigarettes stood for Futagawa{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s initials...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:57.90,0:15:00.90,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,She'd have quite a motive for taking revenge
Dialogue: 0,0:15:01.30,0:15:03.00,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,on the man who killed her old flame.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:03.10,0:15:03.70,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Nah.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:03.70,0:15:08.30,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Remember? Nonomiya said she passed the three of us in the woods.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:08.50,0:15:11.80,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,She couldn't have gone ahead of us, met Futagawa{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} at the top of the cliff
Dialogue: 0,0:15:11.80,0:15:13.20,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,and pushed him to his death.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:13.40,0:15:18.90,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,But the three of you rushed over to Futagawa{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} after he fell, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:18.90,0:15:21.60,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Maybe she saw you looking down from the cliff.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:22.00,0:15:26.60,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,From the top of the cliff, all she would have seen was the tiny dots of our three flashlights.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:26.90,0:15:30.40,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,There's no way the killer could know which three people were standing at the base of the cliff.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:31.30,0:15:33.20,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,In other words, through the process of elimination,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:34.00,0:15:38.10,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Futagawa{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s boss, Editor-in-Chief Heihachi Mikami,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:38.50,0:15:40.80,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,you're the only possible culprit!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:46.15,0:15:49.10,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,So just because the killer isn't one of the other two, it must be me?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:51.20,0:15:55.30,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,But Futagawa{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} was holding seven cigarettes!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:55.30,0:15:58.70,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,That's a message that points to your name, "Heihachi"!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:58.90,0:16:00.10,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Pure chance!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:00.20,0:16:04.10,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Besides, what would my motive be?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:04.20,0:16:08.70,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Especially if he was the one who killed that Kono guy last year.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:08.90,0:16:12.80,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I have no reason to seek revenge for a man I only met once.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:13.60,0:16:14.50,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Right.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:14.70,0:16:19.10,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,But that's only if it was actually Futagawa{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} who killed Kono{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:19.37,0:16:20.40,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,W-What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:20.60,0:16:23.20,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I noticed something when I looked at the guestbook.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:24.20,0:16:27.70,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Mikami{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s name is written {\i1}after{\i0} Kono{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:28.40,0:16:32.70,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Kono{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} had only heard the name Mikami—he didn't know how to spell it.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:33.30,0:16:34.80,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Only heard?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:34.90,0:16:37.30,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,See, Mikami{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s "mi"
Dialogue: 0,0:16:37.30,0:16:39.20,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,is written like the "o" in "o-tearai", right?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:39.20,0:16:39.80,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,"O"?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:39.80,0:16:42.30,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, you usually write it "three" and "up".
Dialogue: 0,0:16:42.80,0:16:43.90,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,How many strokes is that...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:43.90,0:16:44.80,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Uh...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:44.80,0:16:46.70,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,One, two, three...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:46.70,0:16:48.60,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Six!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:49.22,0:16:52.30,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Exactly. The six cigarettes left by Kono{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r},
Dialogue: 0,0:16:52.70,0:16:55.30,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,and the seven cigarettes left by Futagawa{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:56.10,0:17:00.50,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,were both dying messages spelling out the same name—Heihachi Mikami!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:00.76,0:17:04.50,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Futagawa{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} added one to get the correct spelling.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:05.00,0:17:09.20,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,And he probably chose the same brand to let us know the killer was the same person.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:10.00,0:17:14.50,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Come to think of it, when Futagawa{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} was looking at the guestbook, he was smiling.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:14.80,0:17:16.50,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,That's when he realized
Dialogue: 0,0:17:17.00,0:17:20.00,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,that it was Mikami{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} who had killed Kono{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:20.40,0:17:25.70,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,And Futagawa{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} was going to see if he was right.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:25.90,0:17:26.95,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,That's absurd!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:26.95,0:17:28.50,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,What proof do you have?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:29.10,0:17:33.00,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The proof is in this bag from your room!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:33.70,0:17:38.80,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,If we can find the steel pipe you used to bludgeon Futagawa{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} to death,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:39.20,0:17:41.40,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,we'll have all the proof we need!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:42.20,0:17:43.00,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, hey!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:44.20,0:17:47.00,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You already checked my bag!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:47.40,0:17:50.00,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Right. I didn't find a steel pipe.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:50.10,0:17:51.70,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,But I didn't find something else either.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:52.00,0:17:53.00,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Something else?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:53.30,0:17:55.10,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The weight for the telescope.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:56.10,0:17:59.30,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You hid something in the barrel of the telescope
Dialogue: 0,0:17:59.40,0:18:01.20,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,and took the weight out
Dialogue: 0,0:18:01.90,0:18:03.80,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,to bring it back to its correct weight.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:04.60,0:18:07.40,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, want to open the barrel and show us what's inside?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:07.60,0:18:09.70,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,No matter how carefully you cleaned it,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:10.10,0:18:13.70,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,we should still be able to get a luminol reaction from Futagawa{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s blood.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:14.96,0:18:18.50,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It's still covered in the blood of that ungrateful creep.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:18.90,0:18:20.60,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,So you {\i1}did{\i0}...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:21.00,0:18:25.10,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,That's right. I was so good to him—I even made him assistant editor-in-chief!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:25.20,0:18:29.50,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,But he blackmailed me for 50 million yen. I had to silence him.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:30.00,0:18:33.40,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I'd already had to teach Kono a lesson for his ingratitude...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:33.60,0:18:34.60,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Teach him a lesson?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:34.90,0:18:36.10,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,What are you talking about?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:37.20,0:18:38.50,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,A comet...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:41.50,0:18:45.70,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,That day, one year ago, that Kono guy had a request for me.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:45.80,0:18:50.70,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,He wanted me to check whether a comet he spotted was still a new sighting.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:51.10,0:18:54.00,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Then that comet with our name...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:54.80,0:18:59.00,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,He found it. I went up on the cliff to see it for myself.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:59.60,0:19:03.50,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't tell me you killed Asao just to take sole credit for finding the comet?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:03.60,0:19:07.10,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I just wanted my name added along with his.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:07.50,0:19:10.60,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,But that guy... That ungrateful guy...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:11.80,0:19:13.50,Flashback,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}I can't do that.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:14.20,0:19:18.60,Flashback,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}I've already decided to name it the Amatsuchi-Nonomiya-Kono Comet.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:19.50,0:19:21.80,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Then I really...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:22.10,0:19:26.76,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Come to think of it, didn't he say "I finally met the one"?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:27.10,0:19:30.50,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I really thought he had another girl.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:30.50,0:19:34.30,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Discovering a comet was my childhood dream!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:34.50,0:19:37.50,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,But that jerk wouldn't listen!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:38.30,0:19:40.50,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I decided to beat him back to the hostel
Dialogue: 0,0:19:40.90,0:19:42.60,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,and apply for the {\i1}right{\i0} name.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:42.70,0:19:45.80,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,He grabbed me and tried to stop me! I pushed him away,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:46.00,0:19:47.60,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,and he fell off the cliff.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:48.50,0:19:51.80,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,And you came back the next day,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:52.00,0:19:54.90,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,with quicklime to speed up the decomposition.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:54.90,0:19:55.75,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:55.75,0:20:01.30,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,But I never guessed that Amatsuchi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} was the one who sent he invitation.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:01.30,0:20:03.90,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I thought it was part of Futagawa's blackmail scheme.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:04.10,0:20:06.50,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, hurry up with that steel pipe!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:06.50,0:20:07.38,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't rush me!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:07.87,0:20:10.10,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,A steel pipe is a steel pipe...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:11.10,0:20:13.80,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,but this is no ordinary steel pipe!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:13.90,0:20:15.30,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,A shotgun?!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:16.20,0:20:19.00,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Okay, all of you, against the wall!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:20.60,0:20:25.20,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,When I killed Futagawa, I didn't want anybody to hear the shot, so I just hit him.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:25.60,0:20:27.30,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,But this time, I'll just shoot the lot of you.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:27.50,0:20:30.17,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,That's a lot of quicklime.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:33.10,0:20:35.20,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,No need to be afraid, little girl.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:35.20,0:20:38.30,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,In a few moments, you'll be a star in the sky...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:39.19,0:20:40.70,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,What are you doing, kid?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:40.70,0:20:41.90,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Can't you see?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:41.90,0:20:43.10,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm tying my shoes.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:43.10,0:20:43.83,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Shoes?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:44.95,0:20:45.70,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You dumb kid.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:45.70,0:20:47.60,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You think you can run for it?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:47.90,0:20:49.80,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,No. It's just like you, mister.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:50.40,0:20:51.30,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:52.10,0:20:53.20,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,These are...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:53.40,0:20:54.70,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,no ordinary...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:56.60,0:20:57.60,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,shoes,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:01.30,0:21:01.70,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,are they!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:12.70,0:21:14.00,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}I hope you're happy.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:14.80,0:21:17.50,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}You're gonna be a star after all.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:18.30,0:21:21.10,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}A star criminal, that is.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:53.10,0:22:57.40,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,But why was Kono{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} so hung up on using those names for his comet?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:57.60,0:23:00.20,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I can understand Nonomiya{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, because she was his girlfriend.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:00.20,0:23:03.55,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,But if he'd agreed to use Mikami{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s name instead of Amatsuchi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:03.55,0:23:04.62,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,this never would've happened.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:04.62,0:23:08.00,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The three of them had known each other since university, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:08.20,0:23:10.40,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,They must've been best friends!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:10.40,0:23:11.00,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:11.00,0:23:12.50,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't think that's all it was.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:13.30,0:23:15.20,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Those names were perfect together.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:15.60,0:23:16.80,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The "ama" of "Amatsuchi"...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:16.80,0:23:17.80,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,the "no" of "Nonomiya"...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:17.80,0:23:19.60,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,and the "ko" of "Kono", if you put them together,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:20.10,0:23:21.70,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,they spell "Amanogawa", or "Milky Way".
Dialogue: 0,0:23:21.90,0:23:22.60,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I see!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:22.60,0:23:23.30,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You're right!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:23.30,0:23:25.40,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,That's our Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:25.80,0:23:28.60,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, you kids, could you lower your voices a little?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:28.90,0:23:30.70,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Can't believe you called me out here so early.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:30.90,0:23:34.00,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,And I was going to take a day off and visit my grandma out in the country.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:34.10,0:23:35.70,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Now I'll have to put it off for a while.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:36.20,0:23:38.80,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm so sleepy...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:38.80,0:23:39.40,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Where?!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:40.60,0:23:41.90,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Where'd you call just now?!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:42.30,0:23:44.50,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,M-My grandma's place in Tottori...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:44.70,0:23:46.90,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}D-Did he say Tottori?!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:03.70,0:24:04.30,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Ran!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:11.10,0:24:12.40,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Just who {\i1}is{\i0} it?!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:13.70,0:24:15.50,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Damn! Where'd they go?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:19.90,0:24:22.00,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,What's with that siren?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:22.30,0:24:24.00,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't tell me it's...
Dialogue: 0,0:24:30.55,0:24:35.05,Signs,,0000,0000,0000,,Next Conan's Hint:
Dialogue: 0,0:24:30.55,0:24:35.05,Signs,,0000,0000,0000,,Tent
Dialogue: 0,0:24:35.10,0:24:36.80,Dialogue Top,,0000,0000,0000,,Gotta finish this weekend's homework by the time limit!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:36.80,0:24:37.90,Dialogue Top,,0000,0000,0000,,It's already Monday evening...
Dialogue: 0,0:24:37.90,0:24:38.90,Dialogue Top,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh! Gotta watch Conan.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:38.90,0:24:39.80,Dialogue Top,,0000,0000,0000,,It just finished.
